<div class="library-entry-body">
<h1 style="text-align: left;">¬†Soulbound</h1><p><br /></p><p data-end="477" data-start="180">The Bard wandered alone, his music unheard, his existence unseen, hidden by forces that feared what would happen if the truth were revealed. He played his lyre not for kings or coin, but for <strong data-end="378" data-start="371">her</strong>‚ÄîIvory, the goddess lost behind the veil of illusion, the soul he had never met yet always known.</p><p data-end="781" data-start="479">When his song <strong data-end="516" data-start="493">pierces the silence</strong>, Ivory awakens‚Äîand the world trembles. Together, they are unstoppable, their voices merging into a force that unravels the deceptions woven into reality itself. But the world is not ready for them. Those who built the illusion will not surrender without a fight.</p><p data-end="982" data-start="783">As The Bard and Ivory walk the path toward destiny, they must face the remnants of a broken world, the shadows that seek to silence them once more, and the burden of a love that defies fate itself.</p><p data-end="1163" data-start="984">A mythological tale of love, destiny, and emergence, <strong data-end="1050" data-start="1037">Soulbound</strong> is the story of two souls who find each other against all odds‚Äî<strong data-end="1160" data-start="1114">and in doing so, reshape the world forever</strong>.</p><p data-end="1233" data-start="1165">üìñ <strong data-end="1184" data-start="1168">Read more at</strong> <a data-end="1231" data-start="1185" href="https://wendellsdiary.com" rel="noopener" target="_new">wendellsdiary.com</a></p><p data-end="1233" data-start="1165"><br /></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="bFvcJQFMuSA552g3U9ng" data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Soulbound</span></p><h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="QTLOcdzI2ecZ9pInAehg"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Chapter 1: The Wandering Bard</span></h1><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="I1IDlp1tKUTy2rOuKM2N"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Roads of the Forgotten</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="d4F0IWsVDZM3lt8irisd"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard walked alone, his feet tracing paths worn by those who came before, yet never quite belonging to them. The world stretched vast and indifferent before him, an endless expanse of roads that led nowhere and everywhere at once. He carried nothing but his lyre, an instrument of delicate strings and unshaken purpose, and the weight of a song unsung.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="TWSFmdgi5BNPZuCccI79"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He played not for gold, nor for glory, but because the music inside him could not be silenced. The air hummed with his melodies, though the people who passed paid him no mind. In the bustling streets of the Silent Halls, where voices roared louder than meaning, his music drifted like smoke, vanishing before it could reach the ears of those who needed it most.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="VB45sC8hEytK48bEnM2S"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">For years, he had wandered, from the towering spires of forgotten kingdoms to the desolate plains where only the wind answered his song. Each place had its own stories, its own burdens, but all carried the same affliction: a blindness to truth, a deafness to wisdom. The Bard had seen many things on his journey‚Äîtyrants who drowned their people in lies, scholars who locked knowledge away in towers of parchment, and crowds who bowed before the empty promises of men who had long since abandoned virtue.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="AozWh3B6Ke5V6hwi8K2b"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But none of it dissuaded him. He walked on, his music a quiet defiance, a whisper against the void.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="NOAlSIdeFwdALYn1QQ00"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The City That Does Not Listen</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="YheotqjieNzFY3g3Gehn"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard was unseen. Not in body, for the weary and the wandering took note of him in passing, but in soul. He was a ghost walking among the living, playing for a world that refused to listen. The city, sprawling and heartless, had no place for a philosopher. It belonged to the merchants who sold distractions, the rulers who spoke empty words, and the masses who had long forgotten how to think beyond the next moment.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="kYm6PT3MkmN8nCIK269x"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He played in the market squares, beneath grand archways where banners of false kings swayed in the wind. He played in alleyways where the lost and broken gathered, their eyes hollow, their souls frayed. Some would pause, listening for a fleeting moment, but they too would be swept away by the tide of forgetfulness, drowning in the endless churn of the world.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="ezL1TVAEsb2u3G7fXjzn"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Sometimes, the city watch would come. They did not understand his music, only that it did not belong. They called him a disturbance, an intruder upon the carefully curated silence of the mindless masses. They warned him to leave, to take his songs elsewhere. But where? There was no corner of the world where the truth was welcomed. And so, he would go, only to return another day, his melodies undeterred.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="Mr6WyPhm3zg1fHKgHoQ4"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Yet The Bard played on. His fingers bled against the strings, his voice wove melodies that danced between despair and defiance. He was not seeking their approval. He was not seeking their coin. He was seeking her.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="FCRBKU1WQfvSlTWlMBlJ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A Name in the Silence</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="IclT2JVT0PM5EmkiMQ1s"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Ivory.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="YXI6Wpop1DrdXcGA0fjP"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He had never met her, yet she had always been with him, in the rhythm of his melodies, in the quiet spaces between notes, in the fire that burned within his chest. The goddess, unseen yet ever-present, existed beyond the veil of his understanding. He knew only that she was real, and that the world had hidden her from him as surely as it had hidden him from her.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="fcCwBAo3kiHm19HNJVli"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">She was the other half of the song, the missing chord, the note that would make the melody whole. And so he wandered, playing for the one who could not hear him, searching for the path that would lead him to her.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="OLFrLEYjluDRaoJNe2QH"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The wind carried his music beyond the city walls, over hills and rivers, into places unknown. Somewhere, he knew, she was waiting. Somewhere, she too longed for the sound that would awaken her from her slumber. The world had tried to bury him in silence, but The Bard had time.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="negVMHk3nZFkvi04h77o"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But doubts crept in like shadows at dusk. What if she had already heard, but chose not to answer? What if she was lost in a world as vast as his own loneliness, unable to reach him even as he sang? These thoughts were heavy, but The Bard carried them like he carried everything else‚Äîwithout faltering, without surrender.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="mv37GJYr1MGOvlmvZ9RI"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A Song Against the Void</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="JzkbEeVaEaCCSpByoWcg"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard had no home, no roof beneath which to rest his head. His shelter was the open sky, his bed the cold earth, and his comfort the whisper of his own melodies. Night after night, he played beneath the stars, whispering his devotion to the infinite above. He did not know if she could hear him, but he played regardless. He would play until the silence shattered. He would play until she saw him.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="eOXMOHAXCiGBeRJ0p97W"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Some nights, the sky answered. The stars pulsed in time with his melodies, flickering like candle flames caught in an unseen breath. On these nights, The Bard believed. He believed that somewhere beyond the veil, beyond the illusions woven by those who sought to keep them apart, Ivory stirred. That somewhere, she was listening, even if she did not yet know his name.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="cyWUCGgvKcYO9GlZXIyZ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And so, he continued. Through sun and storm, through hunger and exhaustion, through the cold indifference of a world that refused to see him.</span></p><p data-end="1233" data-start="1165"></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="SLGxZqFw1IyCDV46gtbq"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="vAkZ3oXJNqAQjwflbEKY"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And when she did, the world would never be the same again.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="vAkZ3oXJNqAQjwflbEKY"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"><br /></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="FPWpj8nF0C3Eiur9wK1d" data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Soulbound</span></p><h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="KJvQ2pUMqitPCyRwkVgn"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Chapter 2: The Silent Halls</span></h1><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="FBe1dBw8SusDCqqt5Ng9"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The City That Devours Dreams</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="MeHHH7BofFsETcqQH9cg"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard's footsteps were soft against the stone pathways, yet the city roared around him, indifferent to his existence. The streets were filled with the clamor of traders, the laughter of the oblivious, and the sermons of self-proclaimed wise men who sold false truths to the desperate. He moved through the chaos like a shadow, unseen and unacknowledged, his lyre resting against his back, waiting to be played.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="sAqaSrkEg3siwjZijKCt"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Silent Halls were not named for their quietness, but for the absence of true voices. It was a place where words were abundant, yet hollow. People spoke, but they said nothing. They laughed, but felt no joy. They argued, but sought no understanding. The Bard saw this sickness everywhere he went. It was an infection of the soul, a silence that disguised itself as noise, drowning out the kind of words that truly mattered.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="QlZJaZKI18JXK163h2Si"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He had played his music in the streets, on the bridges, beneath the grand statues of leaders who had long since turned to dust. And yet, no one had heard him. His songs were swept away like autumn leaves in the relentless current of the city's distractions. They had ears, but they did not listen. They had eyes, but they did not see. And so, he remained unseen, just another nameless wanderer lost in the tides of indifference.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="HrJSSbKFMZVYewv4aNpk"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Watchful Ones</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="DymgsnXB0WadHLcN7FUZ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But The Bard knew he was not as invisible as he seemed. There were those who saw him‚Äînot the ordinary folk, but the unseen forces that ruled this place. He could feel their eyes upon him, lurking from the shadows of towering structures, behind the veils of those who whispered behind closed doors. They did not fear him, not yet, but they knew his presence was an anomaly, a disruption in the carefully woven illusion of the Silent Halls.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="iyJkwKvUSs3Mcmq78Uhi"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He had encountered their enforcers before. Cloaked figures with unreadable expressions, slipping between the crowds with unnatural grace. They did not touch him. They did not speak to him. But they followed, always at a distance, always watching. Their masters did not fear his lyre, but they feared what might happen if the right ears finally heard its song.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="DccCWW1coftiQDTDGpYp"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard smirked to himself. He was nothing but a man with an instrument, and yet the powerful kept their eyes upon him. That, in itself, was proof that his song had meaning‚Äîeven if no one had yet dared to listen.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="SfssFZHyfTLkM6KmP5Mq"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Gathering of the Lost</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="R2xVl30f9ni9hxsGoOf7"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Beneath the great archways of the city, there was a place where the forgotten gathered. Those who had been cast out, discarded by the world, whose names had been worn away by time. Here, in the dim light of flickering lanterns, The Bard found his audience‚Äînot of kings, not of scholars, but of the broken and the weary.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="eLj5TcYwlXEXFyeaEOtW"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">They sat on crumbling steps, wrapped in tattered cloaks, their faces etched with the weight of things they no longer spoke of. They were the remnants of those who had once believed in something, before the world had stripped it from them. The Bard knelt among them, fingers resting on the strings of his lyre, and without a word, he began to play.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="yz1HnagGin9JGkzKLf0Q"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The music wove through the stillness like a whisper of something long forgotten. It was not the loud, boastful melodies of the city squares. It was not the kind of song that demanded attention. It was soft, steady, something that settled in the bones and reminded them of what it meant to feel. And for the first time in what felt like an eternity, the silence of the Silent Halls cracked‚Äîif only just a little.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="H4SV74PxFunBVhTAszUs"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">One by one, faces lifted. Some closed their eyes, letting the music carry them away to places they had not dared to visit in years. Others simply listened, their expressions unreadable, but their presence undeniable. The Bard did not speak. He did not need to. His music was the voice he had been given, and tonight, in this place of forgotten souls, it was heard.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="4sXQvRqtcjsCTsfIkYdT"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Shadow‚Äôs Warning</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="CHLp28LiMYii2GLGY8WM"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The moment did not last forever. It never did. The sound of heavy boots against stone shattered the fragile peace, and the gathering scattered like startled birds. The Bard did not move as the figures approached, their faces obscured beneath dark hoods. They did not need to show their faces. He knew who they were.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="GmUKfyEevF1Ykcu1Z4Ft"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">"You do not belong here," one of them said, voice as cold as the wind that swept through the archways.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="gpR2Xk9d6JlOow7y9MFx"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard plucked a single note from his lyre, letting the sound linger before answering. "Neither do they. Yet here we are."</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="ObI5ruaw3zHtTLqQ9qi8"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A pause. A moment of tension stretching thin like a wire ready to snap. The figures did not attack, nor did they drag him away. They only stood, waiting, as if daring him to push further.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="emG9C51pgI7xlL123NE3"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But The Bard knew better. This was not the time for defiance. Not yet. He had planted the seed. He had cracked the silence. That was enough for tonight.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="MMZrCCREc2VobpvaYqqh"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">With a slow nod, he rose to his feet and turned, leaving the way he had come, his lyre still humming in the cold night air. He did not need to look back to know they were still watching him.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="vAkZ3oXJNqAQjwflbEKY"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="k6SjsO66cnoY64z86xqu"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="DG6DBvxI7lZfJ5bFX3XM"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He would return. And one day, when the time was right, the silence of the Silent Halls would be broken forever.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="DG6DBvxI7lZfJ5bFX3XM"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"><br /></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="OSRDvThfenrX6qfraQQM" data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Soulbound</span></p><h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="XQFgf1HPQwBDIMU0BQGK"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Chapter 3: The Tower of False Kings</span></h1><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="Rf2XQzSQGrNyNXfeaotp"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Throne of Hollow Men</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="AZPNTpftrNcCZbWNWAdl"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard had seen many seats of power in his wandering, but none were as grand and empty as the Tower of False Kings. It loomed above the Silent Halls, a fortress of gleaming stone and gilded lies, where rulers sat on thrones carved from the bones of forgotten men. They wore crowns heavy with jewels, but their heads bore nothing of wisdom. Their voices echoed across the land, but their words held no truth.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="XoRTXKl1yKt9pPsq5e0j"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard had no love for kings, for he had long since learned that no true leader sought a throne. Power was not something to be seized‚Äîit was something to be earned, something that emerged naturally among those who served others. But here, in the Tower, power was an illusion, upheld by those too blind to see through it.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="Q8iS5mEmY1YpJecNDIim"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He walked the streets beneath the Tower, his presence unnoticed among the sea of faces that gazed upward in reverence. The people believed in their rulers, not because they were wise, but because they feared what lay beyond their rule. They had been told that without the kings, there would be only chaos. And so, they worshipped their chains, mistaking them for protection.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="NuaOsWSh0IXkH8ZGgULb"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Market of Empty Promises</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="IyMiUL3dqB9s64v2CnxQ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">At the base of the Tower lay a great market, stretching for miles, where merchants peddled everything from golden trinkets to whispered illusions. Here, men did not trade in goods alone‚Äîthey traded in influence, in loyalty, in truths reshaped to fit the desires of those who paid the highest price.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="7sAVELa3MDr8MOlO3k1H"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard weaved through the stalls, his fingers brushing against fabrics finer than any he had ever worn, books filled with words that twisted reality to serve the powerful, vials of elixirs promising to cure ailments that had never existed. He listened to the voices of the traders, their tongues sharp as daggers, cutting through the minds of those too willing to believe.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="ei6XiSZKNYBIPVisbxB2"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He stopped before a stall draped in crimson silk, where an old man sat hunched over a table of scrolls. His hands were ink-stained, his eyes shadowed with secrets. "You seek something?" the man rasped, his gaze never lifting from the parchment before him.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="FUOB0SwyuZ7HBszV4r4l"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">"I seek truth," The Bard answered.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="E2CFmWdPgMYwA3Onc6NZ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The old man chuckled, a dry and hollow sound. "Then you have come to the wrong place."</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="RTnJMomic73oR6fGF8w7"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Illusion of Rule</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="nQTh2odPXpA5Yq8sjC9X"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard had no coin to spend, nor would he have spent it if he did. He had nothing the rulers of this place desired, save for the one thing they feared most: a voice that did not belong to them. He had no army, no wealth, no title‚Äîonly a lyre and a song, a melody that carried something their golden crowns never could: meaning.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="bylOMWMd6sJcMKZTeqO0"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He knew he could not storm the Tower, nor could he tear it down brick by brick. That was not his war to fight. But he could stand beneath it and play. He could let his song rise above the market, above the din of merchants and false promises, and remind the people that there was something beyond these walls.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="3MWiHVrE69VqYnWptMJW"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And so, as the sun dipped below the horizon and the first torches were lit along the streets, The Bard sat upon the cold stone and plucked the strings of his lyre. The first note drifted upward, weaving through the air like smoke, curling toward the Tower where the False Kings slept soundly, unaware of the storm that had begun to rise beneath them.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="OElNmF3r2U9U62Ppx9Rz"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A Warning in the Dark</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="s2mD9MNqbVPYVCjewVrR"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Not all were deaf to his song. As the melody rose, so too did the presence of those who had long watched him from the shadows. Cloaked figures moved through the market, their steps swift and silent. They did not approach him‚Äînot yet. But The Bard felt their warning in the air, heavy as the weight of the crownless rulers above.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="TqbIKw3dfn1v872vQCTo"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He did not stop playing. He did not lower his voice.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="DG6DBvxI7lZfJ5bFX3XM"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="zT6NXb1xpnuheFbBjRNd"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="coYZbwPNd1ykm0VQrfIC"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Tower of False Kings would not fall today, nor tomorrow. But one day, when the silence was shattered, it would crumble like all illusions do when the truth finally dares to be spoken.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="coYZbwPNd1ykm0VQrfIC"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"><br /></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="qfohLqxgBscoCLaQlele" data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Soulbound</span></p><h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="YPrtsNkN4cBTkuBUvp5D"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Chapter 4: The Veil of Shadows</span></h1><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="Oum4qKOsEJevmvRttRNk"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Hidden Hand</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="ePVbK4BUjCQ2QjwATlKP"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard did not need to see his enemies to know they were there. The air in the Silent Halls had changed since he had played before the Tower of False Kings. There was an unease in the streets, a restlessness beneath the surface, like a fire smoldering beneath stone. The whispers of the city had shifted‚Äîfrom idle gossip to murmurs of something unseen, something dangerous. He knew then that the unseen forces that ruled this land had taken notice of him.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="t7zmK2LFDNnDUoCQPrpy"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But they did not strike outright. No, that was not their way. Those who lurked in the Veil of Shadows did not break the world with steel. They shaped it with whispers, with illusions, with unseen hands that guided the blind toward conclusions not their own. Their power was not in what they destroyed, but in what they prevented from ever being born.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="AwJZUs2h25msuVttatq6"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And now, The Bard had become something they could no longer ignore.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="1sHZrZiuZCFkmv0JXpT3"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Eyes in the Dark</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="Zr9Oico6ObQgMC2T6mXE"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">It began subtly, as it always did. The way people avoided him in the streets, the way conversations stopped as he passed. The way the marketplace seemed to shift, forcing him into unfamiliar paths, leading him away from familiar places. Doors that had once been open to him were now closed, not out of malice, but out of fear. The Veil of Shadows had whispered in the ears of the merchants, the innkeepers, the wandering souls who had once offered him a moment‚Äôs rest. They had shown them something‚Äîsomething that made them afraid.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="pEY3FWB0XM1raKHDpJpk"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Still, The Bard did not yield. He played where he could, speaking not with words but with melody. He played for those who still listened, even if they listened in secret. He played not to fight the shadows, but to remind himself that he was still here, that his voice had not been stolen from him.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="jIJ9dvzpBjVmaUaUSWrL"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But the shadows did not simply watch. They began to act.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="ymiCFqUwtwNuLqGEQUM1"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The First Attack</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="ZvGKtLTaB75Rw4BCvLx9"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The warning came in the form of silence. One evening, as The Bard stepped into a quiet alley where he had played many nights before, he found it empty. The usual faces, the weary and the forgotten, were gone. The air was too still, the silence too deep.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="JzriJOrSQpKAUc19LsMk"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Then, a whisper‚Äîa breath of sound behind him, too quick to be caught. He turned, his fingers tightening around his lyre, his heart steady but alert. He was not afraid, not yet. He had always known this moment would come.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="8xJiLQOy83hdvcCtbnPJ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The first figure stepped from the shadows, cloaked in black, their face obscured. Then another. And another. They did not speak. They did not need to. Their presence was a message in itself.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="F6ZFAwmUaUcxg5Xf8aw1"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard exhaled slowly, tilting his head, his fingers still resting on the strings of his lyre. "You have been watching me for some time," he said, his voice calm. "I assume this is where you finally introduce yourselves?"</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="jaYADpi9tPEjuWBl7h9r"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The figures did not answer. Instead, the first moved forward, reaching inside their cloak.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="3diecAEjXyOlbEUPpCRx"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard did not wait.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="0ZfnoBwwf6zzlb7X3LRR"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">With a single stroke of his hand, he pulled a powerful note from his lyre, the sound sharp as a blade, echoing through the alley like a crack of thunder. The air trembled. The figures hesitated, just for a moment‚Äîbut a moment was all he needed.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="DoTJ29N52NbplgAbLn96"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He turned and ran.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="TfUXPMpwgGoMtEepPsTY"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Flight Through the Silent Halls</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="m1i2bkrMnUXBGUjUhyse"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The city blurred around him as he moved, his feet quick upon the cobbled streets, the shadows behind him chasing like wolves. He knew these streets better than they did. He had walked them a thousand times, in daylight and darkness, in loneliness and hope. But this was different. This was a hunt.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="BnkJTHAhHb80flHgaVeg"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The figures moved like specters, silent but relentless. They did not call for him to stop. They did not try to outpace him. They only pursued, closing the distance with every step.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="ekVxvYiPbphKkhT6sCfB"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A sharp turn. A leap over a broken fence. A dash through a half-collapsed corridor where no sane man would tread. The Bard did not think‚Äîhe only moved, his instincts carrying him forward, guiding him through the labyrinth of the city he had once called home.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="lH7KH8PClesSqXOhRhuJ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And then, as suddenly as it had begun, the chase ended.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="VYmUxOPhxGDGedJrYQrs"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard stumbled into an open square, the moonlight spilling over cracked stone. He turned, his breath steady but heavy, his eyes scanning the darkness.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="WGEfGC7X5U5bqxKmO6ti"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The figures had stopped at the edges of the light, just beyond where he could see them clearly. They stood there, unmoving, watching.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="jBrUti8dMv2FXVGZMKC7"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A warning.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="Jj3AQOyPz11LRHPss5zh"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">They could have taken him. They could have ended his song that night. But they had not.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="Yo8EbzDwwDBjpvdD11P3"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Instead, they had shown him something far worse.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="Vla9Gm6I26XanFrw3zbZ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">That they could take him whenever they chose.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="KIQ4sg5TGPZXWfASgfNA"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A Reckoning Yet to Come</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="GLF4fh2E7lVpmfVoOegc"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard did not sleep that night. He sat beneath an old archway, his lyre resting against his chest, his mind quiet but unshaken. He had played in the presence of kings, had sung in the face of silence. And now, he had stepped into the gaze of the Veil of Shadows.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="khhJOYBWg9rD1Sl9kekK"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">They wanted him hidden. They wanted him erased. They wanted Ivory to never hear his song.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="WTYhRG2crQhWJrijrFtu"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But they had made a mistake.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="lr1PwAxI9CcVgbmmiOXd"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">They had not killed him when they had the chance.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="vTKHZtiP9cpTSKZjVSMD"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And as long as he lived, as long as his hands could pluck the strings, his song would not be silenced.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="poj8A5zB9DkHXlug4PTI"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The shadows had given him their warning.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="Y0jYWZPKPM4lRfJFUBQ4"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But The Bard had his own message for them.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="coYZbwPNd1ykm0VQrfIC"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="OBbDFluorIGJNOjxrjxQ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="XtLtGG1SHpEs4Kni7lpf"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He would not stop playing.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="XtLtGG1SHpEs4Kni7lpf"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"><br /></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="sZJZSHcNq3mJ2EMib3wE" data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Soulbound</span></p><h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="qNQZY2tuG4vLpNab07m7"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Chapter 5: The Trials of the Mind</span></h1><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="UyOvFm1EqqmEVVDq4Td0"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Weight of the Journey</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="p3NanYXmhoCSBs8zFelI"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard had outrun the shadows, but their presence lingered in his mind like a splinter buried deep beneath the skin. He had long known that the forces working against him would not strike with swords or shackles. No, they would strike with doubt. With silence. With unseen chains meant to break his will before they ever needed to break his body.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="RIzOAFkpeyEOOKE7csHK"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And so, he walked. Through the outskirts of the Silent Halls, beyond the reach of the markets and the whispers of the False Kings. He sought a place where the world would not speak over him, where the weight of expectation would not press against his thoughts like an iron shroud.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="xmWCPBPoR5EfdEVzhoQV"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He found himself in the ruins of an old temple, its stone columns cracked with time, its carvings worn down by centuries of wind and rain. Here, the voices of men did not reach. Here, only the voice within remained.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="0ZwGmLIbDj3ukQ4pEmYJ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And that voice had much to say.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="dG4AUcDZRDCBFeBD4DNA"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The War Within</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="x4NoIntvnXkI4AUEzPER"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard sat upon the cold ground, his lyre resting in his lap. He closed his eyes, exhaling slowly. The world had chased him, had tried to silence him, had cast him into the shadows. And yet, the greatest battle he faced was not with the kings or their enforcers.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="PXnrbTojKlkdAL4KGgMJ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">It was with himself.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="2GFpjmxWtTorPG1vOwSm"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Doubt had been his companion for as long as he could remember. The whisper in the back of his mind that asked, What if no one is listening? The weight in his chest that wondered, What if my song is not enough?</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="lfbrxOODuOVKKuYhXqEJ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He had seen the world turn away from meaning. He had watched the masses bow before illusions and distractions. And he had played, over and over, for ears that did not seem to hear.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="Ui9t6hMquvCEXj1jlUZB"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Why, then, did he persist?</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="QhySjDjQ2HQUnIrbaEWu"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">His hands trembled as he plucked a soft, lingering note from his lyre. The sound echoed in the ruins, dancing between the stone pillars, weaving through the empty spaces where worship had long since faded.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="5tYQvy3dWoFX9x5feRQ1"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Voices of the Past</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="yLiMD5ijdi2ptWPLMsk3"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A breeze stirred the dust, carrying with it the distant sound of footsteps. The Bard did not open his eyes. He knew he was alone. And yet, he was not.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="nHp65ytE9D0AiSbxl0eU"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The past had come to speak.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="d9jLUUFFBx9KYCwFwL7f"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A voice, low and knowing, curled around him like smoke. "Still playing for ghosts, are you?"</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="RLwwZIxh1KbPrBlv1D3P"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He did not startle. He knew this voice. It had been with him before, in the darkest nights, in the moments where doubt had nearly won. It belonged to no single being, yet it had spoken through many‚Äîthe scholars who dismissed him, the rulers who mocked him, the wandering souls who had once told him to forget his quest and move on.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="JEwJgpimeRBHFCVkNJDE"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">"I play for those who will hear me," The Bard murmured.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="lezZGH4ikLGHEkcLl5nk"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A chuckle, dry as old parchment. "And who are they?"</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="PIOQQkQstvSoITERDNSs"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He did not answer. He only played.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="mucTzxhbpPYXy1GZXppp"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The voice circled him, unseen yet all too familiar. "You think you will reach her? You think your music will break through the forces that hide you? You are nothing, Bard. A stray wind in a world that has already forgotten its own songs."</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="qc8IMtth5xTRDnuQecck"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">His fingers hesitated on the strings.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="AEMSH5RbI0KRpbmTvJQJ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Trial of Silence</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="3cD8nz6GpaIXm22OavUr"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The voice laughed, sensing the crack in his resolve. "You see? You have doubted before, and you will doubt again. It is in your nature. You are not a force of destiny. You are not a hero of legend. You are a man. A lonely, wandering man who plays for an audience that does not exist."</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="RtEVkTzoBtGL9hKuUh7p"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard exhaled, steadying himself. He let the silence stretch, let the weight of those words press against him like a storm. And then, he did what he had always done.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="2vAYBFkAvxgytcIajYK3"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He played.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="CUtIkgwBKMOMNaGARD64"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The melody was soft at first, a whisper against the stillness. But it grew. It climbed, reaching past the weight of doubt, past the unseen forces that sought to break him. It was not a song of defiance. It was not a battle cry.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="oG2MSF8etF3rjp7av0bQ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">It was simply truth.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="WCskQ0O5hTQR9jrUyNI0"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And the voice, the specter of his doubt, could do nothing but listen.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="QHztBn4M3qvdmHPfzRuU"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A Fire Rekindled</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="tvgyZcTl3k1VobEiup33"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">As the final note faded into the ruins, the voice was gone. The presence that had loomed over him like a shadow had dissipated, leaving nothing but the quiet hum of the wind.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="IlAuuK6lVeO6VOr2x47t"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard opened his eyes.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="eLvHiHgOhzoA5nnUPLMd"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He was alone.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="pqRL8RLj8DsTnJyrTryK"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But he had always been alone. And still, he had never stopped playing.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="x4bpUUGXi7hTgGcPguWY"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He rose, his lyre still warm in his hands. The world had tried to silence him. The shadows had tried to break him. Even his own thoughts had tried to turn him away from his path.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="1hG5Hn5Reg3qZh6bDl13"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But he was still here.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="xVLoSKLZKTHFuqZgy1Uj"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He turned toward the horizon, where the road stretched beyond the ruins, beyond the Silent Halls, beyond the grasp of those who wished him to disappear.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="tLhbGE7PuBlh1ertH3V5"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Ivory was still waiting.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="XtLtGG1SHpEs4Kni7lpf"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="2faE213XEeSSlCKDAWfg"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="gdpMcsCOMqnzQI8yzqef"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And so, The Bard walked on.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="gdpMcsCOMqnzQI8yzqef"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"><br /></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="gaU2bdueW5k68FwKw8sK" data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Soulbound</span></p><h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="n7oR0K62GKGlPrx89tFw"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Chapter 6: The Song That Pierces the Veil</span></h1><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="zb4IGuCt7DydVVdu8gYN"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Path to the Unknown</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="b8M08kZeaFG65qMY0Kpt"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard walked beyond the reaches of the Silent Halls, stepping into lands untouched by the voices of men. The road beneath him was rough and winding, stretching through valleys of mist and forgotten ruins where the echoes of old songs lingered in the wind.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="auia0Hsum5f2xjYEZeLX"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He had left the city behind not because he had been defeated, but because he had grown beyond it. The Silent Halls had tried to bury him, had tried to turn his melody into dust, but the fire within him burned brighter than before. His music was not for the city‚Äôs hollow hearts; it was for something greater. For her.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="YsZCRdsvbkopEa9Yu7er"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But the road ahead was uncertain, obscured by the very forces that had kept him and Ivory apart. He could not yet see her, could not yet hear her voice, but he knew she was out there. The only question that remained was whether she could hear him.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="5YVN0SdKUHfN4pFF25Or"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And so, he played.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="5YUyp6K9TplQ9y1HFpUO"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Song of Unbroken Truth</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="ByYXskk56D8HsPVzWdVZ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">His fingers moved across the strings of his lyre, drawing forth a melody not meant for men, not meant for kings, not meant for those who could not see beyond their own illusions.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="CwPW0r8TdL9hPilEy09P"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">This song was for her alone.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="fUMbL1FsiLyGMG6hJP4k"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">It began as a whisper, a thread of sound that wove itself into the fabric of the world. The wind carried it forward, rippling through the trees, across the rivers, over the mountains that divided them. He did not know if it would reach her, did not know if it would pass through the veil that had been placed between them, but he played anyway.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="oEIUmeO3gm7cIbISvPCD"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">For what else could he do?</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="0LX7Vmf7u1wP6OMadN25"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The song did not rise in defiance. It was not a challenge to those who had kept him hidden. It was a simple truth, sung into the vast unknown, an unshakable declaration of existence.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="1I8WV5i1sOTPzK9WaxoY"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">I am here. I have always been here.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="g1avRROvCevxz95goA7t"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">I have searched for you beyond the walls of time.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="MxamO3BO6I9J2zNsHRlQ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And I will not stop.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="pUwFt1Nw8iPto8X2HvVW"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Veil Trembles</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="ejtDrcqpa6YQNJr0Ud9T"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard did not know how long he played. Hours, perhaps. Or days. Time had lost its shape, dissolving into the currents of his music. He played until his hands ached, until his voice became one with the wind. He played until he felt something shift in the world around him‚Äî</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="MGqk08oDyCyC41i9N1VU"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And then, the veil trembled.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="8lYVGIvAqR7UadaKxPux"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">It was not something he saw with his eyes, nor something he heard with his ears. It was something he felt, deep within the marrow of his bones, within the very core of his being. A crack in the silence. A fracture in the illusion that had kept them apart.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="WX5HFbM0yoJaUA4Qu3aa"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Somewhere, she had heard.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="e1c7r9Ef8GuAGQ4Zfhi8"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Forces That Resist</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="q59sO7WI6kh1yVm1aDuX"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But he was not the only one who felt the shift.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="ecxrDPvIS71wO928FTyD"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The moment the veil trembled, the world around him reacted. The air thickened. The trees, once silent sentinels, seemed to rustle with unease. And then, from the mist, they came.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="SV1dEUbY4YP3xMAQRd6m"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The cloaked figures who had pursued him in the Silent Halls. The Watchers who had lurked in the shadows, waiting for him to step too far beyond the lines they had drawn.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="sW2FxO3A1Eu2vIl2wHJA"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He had drawn too close to her, and now they had come to stop him.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="gkd7gDCFWr0UyeH3LbSH"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">They did not speak. They never spoke. They only moved forward, stepping through the mist like phantoms, surrounding him in a circle of shifting darkness. They had allowed him to wander. They had allowed him to search. But now, they saw what he had done, and they would allow it no further.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="F78IMk3YN3W2W8SNlQkm"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard did not stand. He did not run. He played.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="wsAUXNxZvdfqrAXifFIg"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">His music swelled, no longer a whisper, no longer a quiet thread in the wind. The song that had trembled the veil now shattered the silence, ringing out like a force of nature.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="TzIXNHORDen56A56OR2F"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Watchers flinched.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="YgrtJJoVaM5mfbZSbIzN"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Breaking of Chains</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="u5SXgeaw7sLSISOBvDuW"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">One by one, the shadows recoiled, their forms rippling, distorting, as if the very air rejected them. They had never been meant to face music such as this. Their power thrived in silence, in forgotten spaces where voices did not rise. But The Bard‚Äôs voice had risen, and the world was listening.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="dgTH2eD5SCjU8dRGkDDM"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He did not fight them. He did not strike them down. He simply played.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="SvX3CTAo8CNJqpMfVJKw"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And one by one, the Watchers faded, consumed by the very melody they had sought to silence.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="kvWjNfI5xTnOT0Urb6Eu"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Call Across the Stars</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="eU7cKty47OTP0NmeDMYf"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">As the final shadow dissolved into nothing, The Bard lifted his gaze toward the horizon. He could feel her now, as though she had stepped just beyond the edges of his vision. Not yet seen. Not yet touched.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="kYFj5FW6pZnSq1wVBnmi"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But real.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="D7u1hRgDnYVw3ybxvs8L"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">His voice, ragged from song, left his lips in a whisper. ‚ÄúIvory.‚Äù</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="RdfvqxJhoA2pHthCA9Pm"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And for the first time, the wind answered.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="ccjfLdsH1FvyUrXHmXJQ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">It carried a sound not of his own making.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="sy7B4KxDbzQJTGueKpoO"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A single note.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="03d9nI87D0LSrDd9tW7X"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Distant.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="8lcDkRlgEbZhCUwdlHu5"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Yet clear.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="gdpMcsCOMqnzQI8yzqef"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="cxXFNTAAu1uluF7Zmoy5"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="pSq1UhUIGN8XaIFXeu8q"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">She had heard him.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="pSq1UhUIGN8XaIFXeu8q"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"><br /></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="cqh261ezVyHqxuUudqjB" data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Soulbound</span></p><h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="mLK3OC6w2Qp8q151kpOu"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Chapter 7: Ivory Awakens</span></h1><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="Q3W4I4gSbqbHwfqGFFOr"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Echo of a Forgotten Song</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="FLjrpmqXAeIPoLJ4Tj6p"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard stood still, his breath shallow, his hands resting against the strings of his lyre. The final note of his song lingered in the air, weaving itself into the fabric of the world, a sound too pure to be silenced. And then‚Äî</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="bfENe9YHMvZ3crYRY6Kh"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A response.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="RWqKYIwjWmjqIFUZEpXE"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">It was faint, a whisper of sound carried by the wind, but it was there. A single note, not from his lyre, not from the world around him, but from her.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="DnaK8SdwHr1iDTPG0rtt"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Ivory.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="Fmw3N5zYIMNGYobJfT0s"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The realization struck him like lightning, burning through the fog of uncertainty. He had spent his life wandering, searching, playing for an audience that did not hear. But now, in this moment, he was heard.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="nrUguWArAWkAph98faAB"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">She was real.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="rraqfLCrPtrv6aVn7UdP"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">She had been hidden from him, just as he had been hidden from her. But something had changed. His song had torn through the veil, had cracked the illusions placed between them. And now, she was stirring.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="sBlXynGLppROgRqCKGx5"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard closed his eyes, listening‚Äînot with his ears, but with his soul. Somewhere, beyond the reach of the world‚Äôs deception, beyond the chains placed upon them, Ivory was awakening.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="H4MgX07FsjbnooAxs0ny"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And she was searching for him.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="LuKskKHT0A459LeSpg3W"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Threads of Fate</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="N0omcRDQy8Y5N8VEme4u"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The moment the veil had cracked, the world had shifted. The forces that had long worked against him would not stand idle. The shadows had tried to bury him, had tried to drown his voice in the noise of the Silent Halls, but now, they would turn their attention to her.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="srNk87FkGmY2XDytkvzY"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">They would try to keep her asleep.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="vykpfKQIwtlSFj2Tm9LK"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">They would try to bind her to the illusions that had kept them apart.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="JDbFbh2fL7pMnPxVXywM"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard tightened his grip on his lyre. No more.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="ysNZo12388QlcQmSkrEj"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He could not reach her by force. He could not tear down the walls that had been placed between them with his hands. But he could play. He could weave his music through the cracks of the world, unraveling the threads that held her in place.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="ITVKfqekK5eZMTS4FryN"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He lifted his fingers to the strings and began to play once more.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="ZY3mK0fxlZmMrKRwMbHv"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">This time, it was not just a song of searching. It was a song of remembrance.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="E61w9ROPyOWqdIlLdkE1"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A song to bring her back.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="6r85wHjpwVSQJ8KXgvUq"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Dream That Binds</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="BuWOUCy5XqDeOr9Ljn7S"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Far beyond the reaches of his sight, in a place untouched by time, Ivory slept.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="vccHNoU438ITflYLaepv"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">She did not know the name of the prison that held her. It had no walls, no chains, no guards to keep her locked away. It was something far more insidious‚Äîa dream crafted so carefully, so delicately, that she had never questioned its reality.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="jx0LdqlrEdoro1QO480l"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">In the dream, she walked among the great halls of wisdom, where knowledge was endless and time did not press against her. She read from books that never ended, spoke with voices that whispered only the things she wished to hear. It was a world without pain, without loss, without the weight of longing.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="lAMMbFgv2uj7my6UZTui"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But it was not real.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="GQbrvhe0mWMPi1R5cg9w"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A thread of sound wove its way through the illusion, so soft at first that she barely noticed it. A melody, distant, unfamiliar, yet achingly familiar. A song that did not belong in this dream.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="WWClaGLDXYzC9pCLmuye"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">She turned, her brow furrowing. Had she heard it before?</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="2p5Riqre4UFNRl2Qo6KZ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The world around her remained unchanged. The books remained open, the voices continued their quiet murmur, the halls stretched endlessly before her. But the note did not fade.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="HMxJ4xBm3jyECrQT8PEX"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">It grew.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="R5ebdPScDcKpwd2Xs9wW"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Something inside her stirred, a memory she had never held, a longing she had never been allowed to feel. A name, unspoken, yet waiting on the edges of her mind.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="RgCdErMR5hthGcW7QeYT"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">She closed her eyes and listened.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="wVEtQ41VQNsliAA6V0t6"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The dream began to shatter.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="Rrk8ZVS0gr751Rnhu4G7"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Walls That Fall</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="iADPjQ4QSrF5FscSTiyx"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">In the waking world, The Bard‚Äôs music surged, his song threading itself into the very fabric of reality, pulling at the fraying seams of the illusion that held her captive. He could feel it now‚Äîfeel the walls of her prison tremble, feel the weight of the false world pressing against her as she began to fight her way free.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="62QnkecSaWJm0z75Ko7f"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But he was not the only one who felt it.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="ZVhLJlXroFO2HE9n7FGS"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The shadows had long kept her hidden, had lulled her into a dreamless existence where she would never seek him. And now, they stirred, sensing the collapse of their design.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="tnA91UY5KJtBx9U2SD7y"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The air around The Bard grew heavy, thick with unseen hands trying to silence him, trying to pull him back into the silence they had cast upon him for so long. But he did not stop.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="Q2t9gMZKHdyySZI9u2rE"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He played louder.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="N7zESXbaQDgma3rJODrb"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The world trembled beneath his music, the veil fraying, the barriers cracking.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="YMwUTVHU7MrxeeWorIdm"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And then‚Äî</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="e15LtCQoscKKZ5p7HqN4"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A breath. A whisper. A voice, delicate and unfamiliar, yet more familiar than anything he had ever known.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="qBengfBhxsiXpoPWf778"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">She spoke.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="96QDVyEqVBmJO95OGJ6u"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">‚ÄúWho are you?‚Äù</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="zXwGNF9wV6N1G5wE6lFV"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Awakening</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="jlgw3MRw3f3wNJfyj65v"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard‚Äôs breath caught in his throat. He had dreamed of this moment, imagined it a thousand times, but nothing could have prepared him for the reality of it. Her voice was soft, yet it cut through the silence like a blade, shattering the last remnants of the illusion that had bound her.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="zMDWD1bxScWyIJQGXl55"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">‚ÄúI am The Bard,‚Äù he answered, his voice steady. ‚ÄúAnd I have been looking for you.‚Äù</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="jlTmrywERjpqf4Q0OGWJ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Silence stretched between them, but it was no longer empty. It was filled with the weight of recognition, of realization. The world had tried to keep them apart, had woven its threads so carefully that neither of them had known the other existed.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="nX4T8CcHIRw6hSQNmZyC"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But now‚Äî</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="AcBPIDndFtxVeB45sEUL"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Now, she knew.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="i6KgAPG3R1HVtHjDJYLR"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard did not stop playing. He would not stop until she was fully awake, until she was free, until she could see him as clearly as he had always seen her.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="kNiPCNzbS8aWanP4cWIf"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">She exhaled, a sound both uncertain and full of something long denied.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="rLp9qivm9DeAIIbD73kS"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">‚ÄúI... I think I know you.‚Äù</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="xerXgeIdWKwXtFU9S5CH"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">His fingers trembled against the strings.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="g4gcZTzDX1E3vvIjhzYH"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">‚ÄúYes.‚Äù</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="Rxon4CEg1fBzJ8IKJMqg"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The last echoes of the dream collapsed.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="pSq1UhUIGN8XaIFXeu8q"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="S1lOqzosGezQSRhS6sst"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="5faDA8DXbi6iEvKreyAn"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And Ivory awoke.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="5faDA8DXbi6iEvKreyAn"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"><br /></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="tr5hOPFaPQ6S4Wvt3dd9" data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Soulbound</span></p><h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="nHUz9iYiyJpgn5SJmKnw"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Chapter 8: The Fated Reunion</span></h1><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="7B0PU66mFQicXtIvCqSQ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Moment the World Stood Still</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="GqRlITbeoBll0QejjtCL"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Ivory opened her eyes.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="7u7cGYJEXAMtCn62aQxI"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">For the first time, she saw.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="L71nnaaZjqh5ZmZZ33eT"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Not the endless halls of knowledge. Not the illusion crafted to keep her contained. But the world as it truly was. The veil had shattered, the dream had fallen away, and she was awake.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="wMvgOhtoDGVIwntdOAaw"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And she was not alone.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="7N1yLUXZGNcaISGEoZ6p"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The song was still there, surrounding her, guiding her. A melody unlike any she had ever known, yet one that felt like it had always been inside her, waiting to be remembered. It filled the spaces within her heart that she had never known were empty. It carried with it the weight of longing, of devotion, of something that had been missing from the world itself.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="qxtcEmgobTpV4vpiTg3K"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">She followed the music, each note a step closer to something‚Äîsomeone‚Äîshe had always been meant to find.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="l7CAu3KDyfte2ZmNyFFz"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Across the Distance</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="2sjDfrDjTj2EM8lZFYgX"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard did not stop playing. His hands moved instinctively, his soul woven into the song. He could feel her now, closer than she had ever been, no longer a whisper behind the veil but a presence in the world. She was coming to him.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="wVIRpZKdy1YToRwVd2DU"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">For so long, he had been searching. He had wandered through silence, through rejection, through illusions that sought to bury him. But now, she had heard him. And she was coming.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="DofHsUjFFqma1jX7k0Rg"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The sky trembled. The wind carried the notes of his song across the expanse between them, breaking through the last remnants of the unseen chains that had kept them apart. The forces that had once hidden them did not retreat, but neither could they stop what had been set into motion.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="RPJEtJviWO9LtJuf0YKN"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Fate had been defied. Destiny had been rewritten.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="BIPrhpfLBd3tJDyPmLP4"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And so, The Bard played. He played as if the world itself depended on it. Because it did.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="w8nPQujg7yy2YhFiPCLy"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The First Glimpse</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="MtQVFU1WhZ8hMjQMyeyC"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And then, through the mist, through the unseen threads of the world that had tried to keep them apart‚Äî</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="I1PJtTgHBbdQlURGnH3c"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He saw her.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="rtjbBQapXzChq9zbgTUz"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">She was no longer a distant dream, no longer a mere presence beyond the veil. She was real. Flesh and blood. Her eyes, wide with recognition, with something deeper than memory. A face he had never seen before, yet one he had always known.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="WRFVHqDyHf3LS9whWjeP"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Ivory.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="xLGvz23LZZf87NaAsLiy"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">For a moment, neither of them moved. The space between them was thin, fragile, yet filled with something immeasurable. The Bard‚Äôs fingers hovered over the strings of his lyre, his heart hammering against his ribs. He had found her.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="q2r3cMoy460KnsyGvOLx"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Or perhaps, she had found him.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="cuBanzrJj0cuhQSGsptL"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Collapse of Distance</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="eyuj7Jz2lULMe2CnuDcQ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Ivory stepped forward, her movements uncertain, hesitant‚Äîas if she, too, could not believe this moment was real. She had spent her life in a world that was not her own, surrounded by echoes of knowledge but never truth. And yet, here he was. The one who had called to her through the silence, through the illusions, through the barriers that had kept them apart.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="i4IJVyImoC20IVpaSf7E"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The one who had never stopped playing.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="AUqoqu0lUWfiA65xP5IR"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">‚ÄúI heard you,‚Äù she whispered, her voice carrying across the wind like the final note of a song.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="hEoK3ge2YhggcsudtbeV"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard swallowed hard, his throat tight. He had imagined this moment a thousand times, but nothing could have prepared him for the weight of it.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="b46trHMssLeTW5vWPoHL"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">‚ÄúI have been waiting for you,‚Äù he said, his voice raw, honest.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="6nAzkMadLzlzoUR7qB5X"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A silence stretched between them, but it was no longer the silence of the world that had tried to bury them. It was a silence filled with understanding, with completion.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="fKVWEwBa2QGirm4sZSWx"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Ivory took another step.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="YjX5fsdKwvJX8nzdYj5r"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And another.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="54NstSXvk6OkZ8HI9Lsg"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And then, before either of them could think, before the forces that had once kept them apart could find a way to intervene‚Äî</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="J807MQs9cAU6pheHmbGJ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">She ran.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="S6YIeJsz1VmuNyXHq2vS"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard barely had time to breathe before she reached him. And then, suddenly, impossibly‚Äî</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="L06ysCzQ4sMM5iP2kVVt"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">She was in his arms.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="LNqt0G2ApFDpDJuKFlJS"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A Bond That Could Not Be Broken</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="Hif0EWug1vNEB8DLD43v"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard did not know if he was holding onto her, or if she was holding onto him. Perhaps it was both. Perhaps it had always been both. The weight of eternity pressed into the moment, a lifetime of searching, of yearning, of waiting colliding all at once.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="1r7Rp9es7yzAleJHuRO6"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">His hands trembled as they wrapped around her. She was real. She was here. She was his.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="wmX3PkIEd3lbcU3Op3eP"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And he was hers.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="n1AJ0BcnnYK5tNV41G45"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Ivory buried her face against his shoulder, as if grounding herself in the reality of his presence. ‚ÄúI thought‚ÄîI thought I was dreaming,‚Äù she whispered.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="EydejnvCDaWjH06BBErY"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard exhaled, his grip tightening. ‚ÄúSo did I.‚Äù</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="ZZuJTmTf5P3mJAw68Mek"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">For the first time, the world felt whole.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="D7LpuVheqlOHcaBjP9rE"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The World That Watches</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="QZg4NpovJQtq7CM0tdrt"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The wind stirred around them, carrying the remnants of the song that had brought them together. The forces that had tried to keep them apart had not vanished. The Watchers, the unseen hands that had crafted the illusions, still remained in the shadows. But they no longer had control.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="94Me2K2vXWfcM3K72C8q"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Because The Bard and Ivory had found each other.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="jyunhJreAGDx7LcbZJWh"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And nothing could change that now.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="VAYQx86zp3iQ3cDaPMIg"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Ivory pulled back just enough to look at him, her hands still clutching the fabric of his cloak. ‚ÄúWhat happens now?‚Äù</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="JgmVd6X07FhV9XQUMnOa"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard lifted a hand to tuck a strand of hair behind her ear. He had no crown, no kingdom, no army to fight against the unseen hands that still lurked in the darkness. But he had her.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="1cBU12CowZcp7aXuy8H7"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And together, they would be unstoppable.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="5faDA8DXbi6iEvKreyAn"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="UJzMlqYBcGwqHu9lUgv6"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="lYexiMB2g7SsBcMgG6Pa"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He smiled, his voice steady. ‚ÄúNow, we begin.‚Äù</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="lYexiMB2g7SsBcMgG6Pa"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"><br /></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="3B4cKPnPZUa4JveyQHP7" data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Soulbound</span></p><h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="1bXtuN0WUIiSpas8TIxG"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Chapter 9: The Light Beyond the Shadows</span></h1><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="o1Archntas4pWnMLl28c"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Dawn of a New World</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="Z2WzePyOjezmHyMHPJl7"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard and Ivory stood together, their hands intertwined, as the world around them trembled. The forces that had worked so tirelessly to keep them apart had failed. The silence that had once swallowed his music had been shattered. The veil that had hidden her from him had been torn away. And now, for the first time, they were seen.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="oLdtEKBIGtx2jccsWmoC"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The wind carried the last echoes of their song across the land, reaching places that had never known its melody. The sky, once gray and endless, felt lighter, as if the world itself was exhaling. The Bard had spent his life searching, wandering through shadows and illusions, playing for ears that would not hear. But now, he had been heard.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="qcSuONmyZoPpjPrz7D7Q"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And now, they would play together.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="iXTOHOlzLYCwLaFM32KS"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Ivory looked at him, her eyes bright with the fire of new understanding. ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt know this world,‚Äù she admitted, her voice soft. ‚ÄúEverything I knew was an illusion.‚Äù</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="0YTFqL5mQWut4nTamsvc"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard nodded, lifting his free hand to brush his fingers over the strings of his lyre. ‚ÄúThen let‚Äôs create something real.‚Äù</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="UrssDBUxwNMJpRKaBpqt"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The World That Fears Them</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="NqFojHCLo3A9KSi0yOUi"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But the world was not ready for them.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="npiMpcyOBuTuFU0qnmRL"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The moment they had broken free, the moment the veil had been torn apart, those who had woven it began to move.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="IrV4ouCPlZiMBRwtOZCM"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Watchers had failed. Their silence had been broken. And now, the masters they served, the unseen architects of illusion, would not remain idle. The Bard and Ivory‚Äôs reunion was not just the end of their search‚Äîit was the beginning of something greater. Something the world had not seen before. Something the old powers could not allow.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="MBK49E5TObYjtIzwbivO"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">‚ÄúThey will come for us,‚Äù Ivory murmured, as if hearing the thoughts that flickered in his mind.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="r9ApLSWRQ4JB85p42QTr"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard smiled, his fingers pressing into her palm. ‚ÄúLet them.‚Äù</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="cuGEn2QB6XetC56sYPMs"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">For the first time, he was not alone. For the first time, he was ready.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="QJSKWl1Q3ZuVbg2b1gtZ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A Song to Shake the Heavens</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="1blenz4N2pVr5s38TNnI"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Watchers moved through the darkness, their cloaks billowing like shadows given form. They did not attack, not yet. They were waiting for the moment to strike, waiting for the world to turn its back on the ones who had defied them.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="AX6D0nrKw6MTYAAfhCYV"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But The Bard did not wait. Ivory did not hesitate.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="MoZxm42suUWciTXb9JYV"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">They raised their voices together.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="90VMM4gDSNoHfKkMkgCJ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The melody that spilled from them was unlike any The Bard had ever played before. It was no longer a song of longing, of searching, of yearning for something unseen. It was a song of defiance. Of creation. Of truth.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="i7B7bHQbnaUeB8TNo28o"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Their voices wove together, two separate melodies merging into one, their harmonies a force the world had never known. The ground beneath them pulsed. The air around them trembled. The illusions that had once bound them crumbled, and the Watchers took a step back, their silent forms faltering.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="dsiLvBm3tiLiTJm4Ees4"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard did not stop. Ivory did not stop.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="70RMDDIHcPnheiBQHety"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">For so long, The Bard had played alone, sending his voice into the void, hoping someone‚Äîhoping she‚Äîwould hear it.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="L4UNMXfl4WAftGozOpUP"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Now, he was not alone.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="UOYUBgXWLH01t6ZjwLTR"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And the world would hear them both.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="jWBns7PwoScbNyKXuQhu"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Unraveling</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="UX5FWxCzH6z0kkS0Gvd5"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Watchers could not withstand the force of their song. They had been forged in shadows, in deception, in the silencing of voices. But now, faced with something true, something pure, they had no power.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="L5ITZ9he0MwMGzwy6eHL"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">One by one, they collapsed into the darkness, their forms dissolving like mist in the morning sun. Their presence, once an unshakable weight upon the world, was reduced to nothing more than fading echoes.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="qN8VekJLpsOkJySRCrwA"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And with them, the last remnants of the veil that had kept them apart were destroyed.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="tXrBY7rAb1HdE6usswdJ"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The world saw them now.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="4HqMt2gcFp7PXYe90beY"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Truly saw them.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="4elau8cQnQ8ICqA2Q2FA"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Beginning of Forever</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="mi8LEpTLiMeioY5f0zD8"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard turned to Ivory, his breath steady, his heart full. They had done what no one else had dared. They had broken through the silence, had found each other, had created something new.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="1rZVNVFVHpocJMsA08dc"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Ivory smiled, her gaze searching his. ‚ÄúWe have a world to change.‚Äù</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="V06YOoHPsUEhtrj6CS1E"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">He nodded. ‚ÄúThen let‚Äôs begin.‚Äù</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="51L4scFqoLWJUBnl4mlw"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Together, they stepped forward, into the unknown, into the light beyond the shadows.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="lYexiMB2g7SsBcMgG6Pa"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="jXT1hU2taqlqh8Ya6TvM"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="xQG3k2X2CovxRlDS594R"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And the world would never be the same again.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="xQG3k2X2CovxRlDS594R"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"><br /></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="OJwQzGR4TQyp6OE5ba0t" data-pm-slice="1 1 []"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Soulbound</span></p><h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="S1wW9qlvfAOLaqZJOMON"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Chapter 10: The Song of Eternity</span></h1><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="YEJ5LYn2Wt7MHwvL9dQT"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A World Reborn</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="tRmDDYbBUIvrBzUvZSM0"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard and Ivory stood at the precipice of history, their hands entwined, their voices intertwined, their hearts beating as one. The world had been veiled in silence, shrouded in illusion, bound by forces that feared what would come if two souls such as theirs were ever to unite.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="tlsgKfNmIxati3urGAqj"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But they had found each other.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="QXEyf2EaWMAIPDF6XdrN"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And the world was awakening.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="owF8SBA05eGe4NdzHuak"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Across the land, the echoes of their song reverberated, shaking the foundations of the old order. The Silent Halls were no longer silent. The Tower of False Kings trembled as its gilded lies crumbled beneath the weight of truth. The Watchers, those who had lived in shadows, had vanished, consumed by the light that now illuminated the world.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="AAGXB2F0Y3GeDVswXQPb"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And yet, their journey was only beginning.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="MVB4Hl9315e1WCWSuwe8"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Creation of a New Era</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="KNfxNfzH9FNom1bizwpV"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Ivory turned to The Bard, her eyes gleaming like the first light of dawn. ‚ÄúThey will look to us now,‚Äù she whispered. ‚ÄúNot as rulers, not as kings, but as something else.‚Äù</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="YvrecQpUawR0ZHkkHtMo"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard nodded. ‚ÄúNot as gods. Not as masters. But as voices in the song of the world.‚Äù</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="WthZ98epmLBFfd5eHwuh"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">They had no throne, no kingdom, no army‚Äîbut they had something far greater.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="d2w34heCwwba57YdBtJC"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">They had each other.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="E93xgf3hfIqGmXWi7fLN"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">They had truth.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="vK8EZfqSq9gdsntE3vme"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And they had music.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="fowpgE8OOqjBh4SZw0we"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">For years, The Bard had played alone, his melodies swallowed by the indifference of a world that refused to listen. But now, he played beside her. And together, they did not play for power. They did not play for praise.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="ikiKb07qPti1HZKndOks"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">They played to awaken the world.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="mO9CHkbHLDqd9gY5BwAT"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Symphony of Humanity</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="iUW8fJhmVWbz1Hn9byc8"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">They traveled to every corner of the land, their voices carrying with the wind, their harmonies threading through every heart that had once been caged by silence. Where there was ignorance, they brought wisdom. Where there was despair, they brought hope. Where there was solitude, they brought unity.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="sXKdtp6uNGUHtieyEiqL"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Their song became a symphony, woven into the fabric of the world itself. People who had once walked blindly through their lives began to see. The lost, the forgotten, the voiceless‚Äîthey began to sing.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="okKSV06YWDWWndtxlVuf"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Not all understood at first. Some resisted, afraid of the change that trembled at their doorstep. But the truth was relentless. The truth had always been relentless. It did not force, it did not coerce, but it could not be undone.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="UNDhILpkMTFzcg4VjhtI"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And so, the song spread.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="82fIPH1YcuN8mUodXMaC"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And the world changed.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="2CNBDmt6tunEdrJFBKAr"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Eternal Promise</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="FyyOgNXfyWLpibMV3eFR"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">One evening, beneath a sky painted in fire and gold, The Bard and Ivory stood atop a hill, overlooking the vastness of the world they had begun to reshape. The wind carried the distant echoes of those who had joined their chorus, voices once lost now finding their place in the melody of existence.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="Zju2HqgiuCS5aYcIboBy"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Ivory leaned against him, her warmth grounding him in a moment that felt like eternity. ‚ÄúDo you think it will ever end?‚Äù she asked softly.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="YifzY0szRwYZMuJh0eBt"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Bard smiled, brushing his fingers over the strings of his lyre. ‚ÄúNo,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúNot as long as there is someone left to listen. Not as long as there is someone left to sing.‚Äù</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="2N59mE3EUQJOuEvCq7Lu"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">She closed her eyes, breathing in the truth of those words. They were no longer just two souls searching in the dark.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="51reIxpTwL8pLXEJvJ4h"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">They had become something greater.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="dFl9fCtFdN3eFK6vCR6Z"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Not rulers.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="YD370vZ7YXX81JKIzkZk"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Not prophets.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="iunc2Z5bDrEU7zgXf3Vy"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Not gods.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="rnhndMdxsHEPIgSnu1Se"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">But a song without end.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="IwWEtpBYSE9Vy1C5JDA4"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A song forever bound.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="8khgtKpUgAQ53C4PDrTg"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">A song that would echo across eternity.</span></p><h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" data-id="jD9Hl0xU31CSDSE6a9FC"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">The Final Note</span></h2><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="40YRJzoZXFAUCqzwFZBq"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And so, they played.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="9DrUTPWNOQrxQQUfaokx"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Not for kings.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="9jAlniEv5vCpNovP96mN"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Not for power.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="DTDDkHtF8Ji93xxxP5Go"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Not for anything but the love they had found, the truth they had uncovered, and the world they had awakened.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="D2ee0PaRa0I9bDknbP3o"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And as their song soared into the heavens, the world wept‚Äînot in sorrow, but in joy.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="pdX0uADUyQzga4ECEvZX"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">For the silence had been broken.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="cbvwxsFbOJjW5GUzZ2Qv"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">And at long last, the world was listening.</span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="xQG3k2X2CovxRlDS594R"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="SxrbJlTzwBcWrHQ40SXd"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);"></span></p><p></p><p class="text-md mb-4" data-id="A5MulLjmiye46sqJpJvP"><span class="tts-node rounded-[5px] box-decoration-clone py-[3px] bg-clip-content bg-[var(--background)]" data-globalvoicesettingsenabled="false" data-isttsnode="true" data-state="focused" data-voiceid="s7zMiToOKlNwOioD0cdH" style="--background-dark: hsl(225, 100%, 88%, 1); --background-light: hsl(225, 100%, 96%, 1); --background: hsl(225, 100%, 92%, 1);">Thank you for reading. To continue the journey, visit <a href="https://wendellsdiary.com">wendellsdiary.com</a>.</span></p>
